The world-renowned Calabar carnival is set to return in December 2022. The carnival was approved to return by the Cross River State EXCO in the government house in Calabar recently. Commissioner for Culture and tourism, Eric Anderson moved the motion for the return of the carnival and it was duly approved by members of EXCO.   Edochie’s first wife shrugs off marriage drama     Faze, Konga, others thrill at Ruggedman’s Foundation night     Adaorah shines at BET awards   The Government had to shut down carnival activities for the past two years due to COVID-19, but the council also made a case for the return after the seeming curtailing of COVID-19. The governor is also said to have given the marching orders to begin preparations in earnest. On what to expect in this year’s carnival, Anderson said “We have had a two-year hiatus so we will be coming up with a bumper carnival program.”